### Create an order (Azure Functions local)
POST http://localhost:7071/api/orders
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "eventId": "673d8b5c-ae59-4bb9-891d-527a109c2be8",
  "attendeeName": "Alice Example",
  "attendeeEmail": "alice@example.com",
  "ticketPrice": { "amount": 2500, "currency": "USD" },
  "simulatePaymentSuccess": true
}

### Example using `curl`
# curl -X POST http://localhost:7071/api/orders \
#   -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
#   -d '{"eventId":"<event-id>","attendeeName":"Alice Example","attendeeEmail":"alice@example.com","ticketPrice":{"amount":2500,"currency":"USD"},"simulatePaymentSuccess":true}'
